exercise.p:
Check the presentation for errors. If you find one, circle it and describe the mistake in words. 

	\begin{aligned}
	\frac{4}{5} + \frac{3}{7} \amp = \frac{4}{5} \cdot 7 + \frac{3}{7} \cdot 5 \amp \amp \text{Common denominator} \\
	\amp = \frac{28}{35} + \frac{15}{35} \\
	\amp = \frac{43}{35} 
	\end{aligned}
